<h2>Calculator Inputs Explained</h2>
<p>Understand each input to get the most accurate results</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>GMV So Far</strong> (Required) - Total gross merchandise value driven through your affiliate links this month - Example: £8,000</li>
<li><strong>Day of Month</strong> (Required) - Current day of the month, used to project your full month earnings - Example: Day 15</li>
<li><strong>Commission Rate</strong> (Required) - Your average commission percentage across products you promote - Example: 8%</li>
<li><strong>Agency Fee</strong> (Required) - Percentage your agency takes from your commission earnings - Example: 20%</li>
<li><strong>Refund Rate</strong> (Required) - Percentage of sales that get refunded, removing your commission - Example: 8%</li>
</ul>
<p>TikTok Shop settlement is based on delivery confirmation, not the sale date. Payouts are typically initiated 15 days after the buyer confirms delivery, which means your actual cash arrives weeks after the sale.</p>
<h2>How TikTok Shop Settlement Works</h2>
<p>From sale to payout in your account</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Day 1</strong> - Customer places order - Your affiliate link tracks the sale and commission is recorded as pending.</li>
<li><strong>Day 3-7</strong> - Order delivered - Courier delivers the product. The settlement clock starts from confirmed delivery.</li>
<li><strong>Day 7-21</strong> - Return window - Buyers can return the product during this period. Duration varies by category.</li>
<li><strong>Day 15+</strong> - Payout initiated - After delivery confirmation, TikTok begins processing your payout. This is not instant.</li>
</ul>
<p>Commission is estimated until settlement is final. Your pending balance may change as returns are processed.</p>
<h2>Understanding Your Deductions</h2>
<p>What comes out of your gross earnings</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Refunds (5-10%)</strong> - Full refunds remove your commission entirely. Partial refunds reduce your commission proportionally. This is the most unpredictable deduction.</li>
<li><strong>Agency Fee (15-30%)</strong> - Typically taken from your commission earnings, not from the total GMV. Make sure you understand whether your agency takes a cut before or after refunds.</li>
<li><strong>TikTok Platform Fee</strong> - Already factored into the commission rate. TikTok takes their platform fee from the seller, not directly from the affiliate. Your commission rate is what you actually receive.</li>
</ul>
